article.headline: Albany, N.Y. 48, St. Francis, Pa. 0
article.story: ALBANY, N.Y. -- Dan Di Lella threw two touchdown passes and Dillon Romain ran for two scores as Albany (N.Y.) shut out St. Francis (Pa.) 48-0 on Saturday. The Great Danes (3-2, 1-1 Northeast Conference) scored on four of their first five possessions en route to a 24-0 halftime lead. Di Lella, who was 16-for-20 for 170 yards, hit John Lullen with a 15-yard scoring pass in the first quarter and threw a 2-yard TD pass to Paul Booker in the third. Romain, who had 15 carries for 58 yards, had scoring runs of 2 yards and 1 yard. The Great Danes rolled up 417 total yards while holding the Red Flash to 81 yards, 29 passing and 52 rushing. Drew Smith had a 17-yard touchdown run and backup QB Buddy Leathley threw an 8-yard TD to Rhakeem Wiggins. Herb Glass had field goals of 45 and 42 yards. St. Francis (1-3, 1-2) lost two fumbles and had only three first downs.
